Program: Omnibus
Title: Nuclear Waste and the Apache
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376kjb
Last Broadcast Date: 09 February 1993
The grandson of Geronimo, Joseph Geronimo explains why he is leading the opposition to plans by Mescalero Apache tribe leaders to lease land for the storage of nuclear waste in sacred ground within the reservation in New Mexico.